\title{Limited Principle of Omniscience}
\date{2023-10-14}
\taxon{definition}
\author{Douglas S. Bridges}
\author{Fred Richman}

\def\NN{\mathbb{N}}

\p{
  The \em{limited principle of omniscience} (often abbreviated as \b{LPO}) says
  that, for any binary sequence #{\{ a_n \}_{n \in \NN}}, either there exists
  some #{n \in \NN} such that #{a_n = 1} or #{a_n = 0} for all #{n \in \NN}.
}

From page 3 of [Varieties of Constructive Mathematics](bridges-richman-varieties).
